002846", "name": "Associated raw file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_8.raw"}, {"accession": "MS:1002851", "name": "Other type file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_description.docx"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/tonoplast_no_ratios.mzML"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_1.mzML"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_2.mzML"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_3.mzML"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_4.mzML"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_5.mzML"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_6.mzML"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_7.mzML"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Sample_8.mzML"}, {"accession": "MS:1002848", "name": "Result file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289/Results_file.mzid.gz"}], "description": "Fruit taste is determined by sugars, acids and in some species, bitter chemicals. Attraction of seed-dispersing organisms in nature and breeding for consumer preferences requires reduced fruit bitterness. A key metabolic shift during ripening prevents tomato fruit bitterness by eliminating \u03b1-tomatine, a renowned defence-associated Solanum alkaloid. Here, we combined fine mapping with information from 150 re-sequenced genomes and genotyping a 650 tomato core collection to identify nine bitter-tasting accessions including the \u2018high \u03b1-tomatine\u2019 Peruvian landraces reported by Rick and colleagues (1994). These \u2018bitter\u2019 accessions contain a deletion in GORKY, a nitrate/peptide family (NPF) transporter mediating \u03b1-tomatine subcellular localization during fruit ripening. GORKY exports \u03b1-tomatine and its derivatives from the vacuole to the cytosol and this facilitates the conversion of the entire \u03b1-tomatine pool to non-bitter forms, rendering the fruit palatable. Hence, GORKY activity was a significant innovation in the process of tomato fruit domestication and breeding. The experiment was carried out to further prove that GORKY is localized to tonoplast in ripe fruit.", "fullDatasetLinks": [{"accession": "MS:1002852", "name": "Dataset FTP location", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2021/01/PXD023289"}, {"accession": "MS:1001930", "name": "PRIDE project URI", "value": "http://www.ebi.ac.uk/pride/archive/projects/PXD023289"}], "identifiers": [{"accession": "MS:1001919", "name": "ProteomeXchange accession number", "value": "PXD023289"}, {"accession": "MS:1001922", "name": "Digital Object Identifier (DOI)", "value": "10.6019/PXD023289"}], "instruments": [{"accession": "MS:1001911", "name": "Q Exactive"}], "keywords": [{"accession": "MS:1001925", "name": "submitter keyword", "value": "tomato, fruit, SGA, bitter, transporter, NPF"}], "modifications": [{"accession": "MOD:00397", "name": "iodoacetamide derivatized residue"}], "publications": [{"terms": [{"accession": "MS:1002858", "name": "Dataset with its publication pending"}]}], "species": [{"terms": [{"accession": "MS:1001469", "name": "taxonomy: scientific name", "value": "Solanum lycopersicum"}, {"accession": "MS:1001467", "name": "taxonomy: NCBI TaxID", "value": "4081"}]}], "title": "The GORKY Glycoalkaloid Transporter is Indispensable for Preventing Tomato Bitterness"}